Rating: 4
This is a very unique cake, so I love making it for special occasions. Surprisingly, it is not as sweet as most cakes, but it is still very rich and delicious, plus I prefer cakes that taste like something other than sugar. Sometimes I use instant coffee instead of instant espresso powder for the icing, which I make BEFORE THE CAKE. If the icing isn't setting properly, I just put it in the fridge for up to 30 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes. For the coffee, I often make an americano (espresso + water), but it is important not to make the coffee too strong, otherwise the flavor is overwhelming! Unlike other reviewers, this case has never come out dry for me, it is always very moist. I am not a huge fan of really rich chocolate, though, so I sometimes use lighter chocolate to give it a slightly lighter, slightly sweeter flavor.

