Rating: 4
Flavor was same as the slice eaten at Barrington Brewery! Hunted for a recipe online & found several that were identical, except for the addition of the expresso, which the Brewery does NOT add to their cake. I WANT TO SHARE A COUPLE MISTAKES I MADE: 1. My cake came out too dry. It should be dense, & slightly moist. I halved the recipe & used a 10" spring pan. The toothpick wasn't clean after 35 mins (no surprise as I poured all the batter into this one pan) So I baked 5 mins more but still not quite clean. Instead of checking cake after 1 more min, I set the timer for another 5 mins, when the cake likely needed just 1 more min! So lesson learned! 2. FROSTING: Never got thickened all the way (wrong chocolate used? recipe says nothing about brands to use/avoid. I used a bar of Godiva 80% cacao bittersweet plus semi-sweet vegan morsels = great flavor!) BUT I heated the cream past the point of simmer (by accident). There is no warning about heating past simmer in the recipe but I think this is reason for my problem. OR perhaps chilling in a non-metal bowl hurt the thickening ability? (again, no mention in recipe) Ganache is new to me, so not sure & only guessing here. Some recipes say to pour hot cream over the chocolate & wait one minute. Is this a key factor missing in this recipe? So, more info needed about mixing the cream & chocolate, & whether to whip/mix/beat once thickened or do nothing. Mine still not thick after 8 hrs so used freezer so something not right. So, gave up, frosted cake & put in fridge overnite. Delicious today, but cake a bit too dry & icing should be bit thicker to duplicate Brewery cake I ate. Will try again & hope I have better luck with lessons learned by trial!

