Made this cake for a birthday. The cake is very good with a light spongy texture...almost a sponge cake. I would make the cake again and possibly in a bundt pan. The frosting on the other hand is another story. I used the Trader Joe's pound plus for the 16oz of choc. for the frosting. That is a alot of chocolate. The recipe recommends chilling the frosting for about 2 hrs. stirring occasionally. At the 1hr. stir I could barely move the whisk the chocolate had solidified so much. I removed the frosting from the fridge and the cakes where still slighty warm so with some coaxing I was able to frost the entire layer cake. It was a good thing I put the candles in ahead of time, right after the frosting job. A few hours later those candles were cemented into the solidified "frosting". The frosting does melt in your mouth rather like a rich chocolate bar. The cake certainly had a hard candy coating. The frosting is so rich and chocolate bar like that it is difficult to eat very much of it.

